register.description: Programming Control Register
The TRCSTATR indicates the ETM-Teal status

bitfield.description: Indicates whether the ETM-Teal registers are stable and can be read
Indicates that the trace unit is inactive

register.description: The TRCCONFIGR sets the basic tracing options for the trace unit
The TRCEVENTCTL0R controls the tracing of events in the trace stream. The events also drive the ETM-Teal external outputs.

bitfield.description: Selects the resource type for event 1

Selects the resource number, based on the value of TYPE1: When TYPE1 is 0, selects a single selected resource from 0-15 defined by SEL1[2:0]. When TYPE1 is 1, selects a Boolean combined resource pair from 0-7 defined by SEL1[2:0]
Selects the resource type for event 0

Selects the resource number, based on the value of TYPE0: When TYPE1 is 0, selects a single selected resource from 0-15 defined by SEL0[2:0]. When TYPE1 is 1, selects a Boolean combined resource pair from 0-7 defined by SEL0[2:0]

register.description: The TRCEVENTCTL1R controls how the events selected by TRCEVENTCTL0R behave

bitfield.description: One bit per event, to enable generation of an event element in the instruction trace stream when the selected event occurs
One bit per event, to enable generation of an event element in the instruction trace stream when the selected event occurs

register.description: The TRCSTALLCTLR enables ETM-Teal to stall the processor if the ETM-Teal FIFO goes over the programmed level to minimize risk of overflow

bitfield.description: Prioritize instruction trace if instruction trace buffer space is less than LEVEL
Stall processor based on instruction trace buffer space
Threshold at which stalling becomes active. This provides four levels. This level can be varied to optimize the level of invasion caused by stalling, balanced against the risk of a FIFO overflow

register.description: The TRCTSCTLR controls the insertion of global timestamps into the trace stream. A timestamp is always inserted into the instruction trace stream

bitfield.description: An event selector. When the selected event is triggered, the trace unit inserts a global timestamp into the trace streams

register.description: The TRCSYNCPR specifies the period of trace synchronization of the trace streams. TRCSYNCPR defines a number of bytes of trace between requests for trace synchronization. This value is always a power of two

bitfield.description: Defines the number of bytes of trace between trace synchronization requests as a total of the number of bytes generated by the instruction stream. The number of bytes is 2N where N is the value of this field: - A value of zero disables these periodic trace synchronization requests, but does not disable other trace synchronization requests. - The minimum value that can be programmed, other than zero, is 8, providing a minimum trace synchronization period of 256 bytes. - The maximum value is 20, providing a maximum trace synchronization period of 2^20 bytes

register.description: The TRCCCCTLR sets the threshold value for instruction trace cycle counting. The threshold represents the minimum interval between cycle count trace packets
The TRCVICTLR controls instruction trace filtering

bitfield.description: In Secure state, each bit controls whether instruction tracing is enabled for the corresponding exception level
In Secure state, each bit controls whether instruction tracing is enabled for the corresponding exception level
Selects whether a system error exception must always be traced
Selects whether a reset exception must always be traced
